VSCode Version: 1.29.0-insider (10/16 build)
OS Version: Win10

The following single-file extension will reproduce this issue:
```
'use strict';

import * as vscode from 'vscode';

export async function activate(context: vscode.ExtensionContext) {
    let documentUri = 'C:/Program Files/Microsoft VS Code Insiders/resources/app/extensions/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts';
    await vscode.workspace.openTextDocument(documentUri);
    await vscode.commands.executeCommand<vscode.CodeLens[]>('vscode.executeCodeLensProvider', vscode.Uri.file(documentUri), Number.MAX_VALUE);
}

export function deactivate() {}
```

Open a file in VS Code with this extension installed. No language services will work (hover, find all refs, go to definition, ...). All will result in "infinite" loading (they do eventually come back online once `executeCodeLensProvider` returns, but this can take ~10 minutes).

This is clearly because of the `Number.MAX_VALUE` argument. If this is set to 10, e.g., things behave fine. My concern is that this is a regression - the current version of stable doesn't have this issue - and I'd like to have all code lenses for the document resolved.

```json
{
    "key": "ctrl+shift+alt+u",
    "command": "editor.action.insertSnippet",
    "args": {
        "snippet": "💄"
    },
},
```
I want to use it for scm inputbox (or find widget).
